Perfect! I can see the issue now. Your textarea is showing plain HTML tags instead of rendering the formatted text with bold and bullet points.

The problem is that **textareas can only display plain text** - they don't render HTML formatting. You need to use a `<div>` with `innerHTML` binding instead.

Here's a solution with a custom Angular component:

## Component TypeScript:

```typescript
import { Component, Input } from '@angular/core';
import { DomSanitizer, SafeHtml } from '@angular/platform-browser';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-formatted-text-display',
  templateUrl: './formatted-text-display.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./formatted-text-display.component.css']
})
export class FormattedTextDisplayComponent {
  @Input() htmlContent: string = '';
  
  constructor(private sanitizer: DomSanitizer) {}
  
  get sanitizedContent(): SafeHtml {
    return this.sanitizer.sanitize(1, this.htmlContent) || '';
  }
}
```

## Component Template:

```html
<div class="formatted-text-display" [innerHTML]="sanitizedContent"></div>
```

## Component CSS:

```css
.formatted-text-display {
  border: 1px solid #ccc;
  padding: 10px;
  background-color: #f9f9f9;
  min-height: 100px;
  width: 100%;
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  font-size: 14px;
  color: #333;
  overflow-y: auto;
  white-space: pre-wrap;
  word-wrap: break-word;
}

.formatted-text-display ul {
  margin: 10px 0;
  padding-left: 20px;
}

.formatted-text-display li {
  margin: 5px 0;
}

.formatted-text-display strong,
.formatted-text-display b {
  font-weight: bold;
}
```

## Usage in your form:

```html
<app-formatted-text-display [htmlContent]="formControl.value"></app-formatted-text-display>
```

Or if you want to keep it inline without a separate component:

```html
<div class="formatted-text-display" 
     [innerHTML]="formControl.value | sanitizeHtml">
</div>
```

**Key points:**
- Use `[innerHTML]` binding instead of textarea
- Sanitize the HTML to prevent XSS attacks
- Style the div to look like a readonly field if needed
- The HTML from your Oracle CLOB (with `<b>`, `<ul>`, `<li>` tags) will now render properly

